    <note>Qian(1) Mingyi [13109] As right policy critic, he impeached Fan(2) Zhongyan [8043] and Fu(6) Bi [628], who were both dismissed. He rose to Hanlin academician and in ca. 1067-8 (when Shenzong became emperor), the censors (yushi) pointed out that he as a client [qingfu: literally leaned upon and adhered to] Xia(2) Song [703] and Jia(3) Changchao [8031] and destroyed correct men (zhengren) [on their behalf]. In addiition, his literary style was shallow and he was not worthy of being a Hanlin academician. Zhejiang TZ, 123.23b. CBD, 5, 4078.</note>
